children.subject: As far as I know, there is no time by which you are required to take EE16A (other than as part of your graduation requirements).

Thanks, Steven and sorry, Anon for missing this question! While the faculty would prefer you to take EE16AB earlier in your academic career, it is not enforced; however EE16AB are pre-reqs for many, if not all, EE/EECS upper div classes.

Are current sophomores (i.e. Class of 2018) students, required to take EE16A next semester? Is there any time limit for current sophomores to take 16A? (Like before a certain semester) 

If we haven't taken 16A/B yet and do not plan to take it next semester, will our enrollment be blocked?

history.content:
Hello,

The post below was emailed to EECS students on Monday. Please read, in case you missed it.

Lydia

-------------------------------------------------

Dear EECS Students,

 
In response to your questions regarding space in EE16A for Spring 2016, we plan to process enrollment in the following way:
  1. EECS majors (all grades)
  2. COE majors: ME, Nuclear, BioEng, and Eng Undeclared (all grades)
  3. LSCS seniors and juniors (by Non-AP level)
  4. Other majors (all grades)
We estimate about 200 EECS majors will need EE16A this spring and have reserved that many seats for you. 
 
Q: Should I use Phase I or Phase II units for EE16A as an EECS student?
 
A: Since these 200 seats are reserved for EECS students, you are able to use Phase II units for EE16A as these seats will be held through Dec 10. However, it is always best practice to monitor the enrollment and change during Open Hours, if needed. 
 
**It is important to note that the seats set aside for lower division EECS classes will be released on December 11.**
Sincerely,
EECS Center for Student Affairs Staff
history.subject: Updated EE16A Spring Enrollment Procedure for EECS Students
